#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/general-style.md:1
msgid "General Style"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/general-style.md:3
msgid "Prefer semantic line breaks (`semantic-line-breaks`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/general-style.md:5
msgid ""
"For prose in Markdown and doc comments, insert line breaks at semantic "
"boundaries so each line carries one coherent idea. At minimum, break at "
"sentence boundaries. For longer sentences, also consider breaking at clause "
"boundaries."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/general-style.md:11
msgid ""
"Semantic line breaks make diffs smaller, reviews easier, and merge conflicts "
"less noisy."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/general-style.md:15
msgid ""
"As an exception, RFC documents that are mostly read-only can use regular "
"paragraph wrapping."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/general-style.md:19
msgid "See also: [Semantic Line Breaks](https://sembr.org/)."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/general-style.md:22
msgid ""
"Make a crate's `README.md` its crate-level documentation (`readme-as-crate-"
"doc`)"
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/general-style.md:24
msgid ""
"A published crate's `README.md` (shown on crates.io) and its crate-level "
"Rust doc (shown on docs.rs) usually carry the same content. Keep a single "
"source of truth: write the `README.md`, and include it as the crate-level "
"doc rather than maintaining a separate copy."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/general-style.md:32
msgid "\"../README.md\""
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/general-style.md:35
msgid ""
"Write the `README.md` so it renders correctly under both a Markdown renderer "
"and rustdoc."
msgstr ""

#: src/to-contribute/coding-guidelines/for-documentation/general-style.md:37
msgid ""
"See also: [Issue #2947](https://github.com/asterinas/asterinas/issues/2947) "
"for the rationale, the caveats, and a template; the [`ostd-pod`](https://"
"github.com/asterinas/asterinas/tree/main/ostd/libs/ostd-pod) crate for a "
"crate that already adopts it."
msgstr ""
